{"title_page": "Pietro Taricone", "text_new": "{{Infobox person\n| name          = Pietro Taricone\n| image         = <!-- filename only, no \"File:\" or \"Image:\" prefix, and no enclosing [[brackets]] -->\n| alt           = <!-- descriptive text for use by speech synthesis (text-to-speech) software -->\n| caption       =\n| birth_name    = <!-- only use if different from name -->\n| birth_date    = {{Birth date and age|1975|02|04}}\n| birth_place   = [[Frosinone]], Italy\n| death_date    = {{Death date and age|2010|06|29|1975|02|04}}\n| death_place   = [[Terni]], Umbria, Italy\n| nationality   = Italian\n| other_names   =\n| occupation    = {{hlist|Actor|television personality}}\n| years_active  = 2000\u20142010\n| known_for     = ''[[Grande Fratello (season 1)|Grande Fratello]]''\n| notable_works =\n}}\n\n'''Pietro Taricone''' (4 February 1975 \u2013 29 June 2010) was an [[Italy|Italian]] [[actor]], [[television personality]], and [[reality show]] contestant on ''[[Grande Fratello]]''.<ref name=maltatoday>{{Cite news|first=|last=|title=Italy mourns 'Big brother' star Pietro Taricone, dead at 35|url=https://www.maltatoday.com.mt/news/world/2196/italy-mourns-big-brother-star-pietro-taricone-dead-at-35#.XnbQP5NKjVo |work=[[Malta Today]]|publisher= |date=2010-06-29 |accessdate=2010-07-06}}</ref> An avid [[athlete]] and [[extreme sport]] enthusiast, he was nicknamed \"O\u2019 guerriero\" ('The Warrior').<ref name=timesofmalta/>\n\nTaricone was born in [[Frosinone]]. He was a contestant on the first season of ''[[Grande Fratello Season 1|Grande Fratello]]'', the Italian version of ''[[Big Brother (TV series)|Big Brother]]'', in 2000.<ref name=timesofmalta>{{Cite news|first=Stephanie|last=Fsadni|title=Pietro Taricone dies in parachute incident|url=https://timesofmalta.com/articles/view/pietro-taricone-dies-in-parachute-incident.315379 |work=[[Times of Malta]]|publisher= |date=2010-06-29 |accessdate=2010-07-06}}</ref> On the show, Taricone had an affair with fellow contestant [[Cristina Plevani]] after just three days in the house.<ref name=timesofmalta/> Taricone came in third place on the show, while Plevani won the season.<ref name=timesofmalta/> However, the show launched Taricone's career and he later appeared in Italian television and film roles.<ref name=maltatoday/>\n\nTaricone had one daughter, Sofia, with [[Kasia Smutniak]], a [[Poland|Polish]] [[Model (person)|model]] and [[actress]].<ref name=timesofmalta/>\n\nTaricone and Smutniak took part in a [[skydive]] over [[Terni]], [[Umbria]], in June 2010.<ref name=maltatoday/> During the jump, Taricone waited to open his parachute until he was just 100 metres from the ground<ref name=maltatoday/> and thus could not stop his fall in time before he hit the ground.<ref name=maltatoday/> He suffered severe back, leg, and head injuries in the accident.<ref name=timesofmalta/>\n\nHe died on 29 June 2010, after more than nine hours of surgery, at the age of 35.<ref name=maltatoday/><ref name=timesofmalta/>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb name|id=0850434|name=Pietro Taricone}}\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Taricone, Pietro}}\n[[Category:1975 births]]\n[[Category:2010 deaths]]\n[[Category:Italian male actors]]\n[[Category:Participants in Italian reality television series]]\n[[Category:Grande Fratello]]\n[[Category:People from Caserta]]\n[[Category:Male actors from Rome]]\n[[Category:Accidental deaths in Italy]]\n[[Category:Big Brother (franchise) contestants]]\n[[Category:People of Abruzzese descent]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox person\n| name          = Pietro Taricone\n| image         = <!-- filename only, no \"File:\" or \"Image:\" prefix, and no enclosing [[brackets]] -->\n| alt           = <!-- descriptive text for use by speech synthesis (text-to-speech) software -->\n| caption       =\n| birth_name    = <!-- only use if different from name -->\n| birth_date    = {{Birth date and age|1975|02|04}}\n| b